OL,6,FIn a letter to the Post Office Horizon
OL,7,FIT Inquiry Chair, Sir Wyn Williams,
OL,8,Fthe lawyer representing the Riddells
OL,9,Fsaid he was told Mrs Riddell had
OL,10,Fdecided before her death to settle for
OL,11,Fthe lower lump sum, despite it being
OL,12,Flikely that she would have been
OL,13,Fentitled to far higher compensation.
OL,15,FThe letter read: "The reason for this
OL,16,Fwas that the family finances were so
OL,17,Fstrained that they could not afford to
OL,18,Fwait."
